<sect1 id="dir_e5090bf757e2582e2690780840c48cfe_1autotoc_md345">
<title>helios::engine::mechanics::timing::commands</title><para>Timer control commands for the command buffer.</para>
<para>This namespace contains command classes used to request timer state transitions through the command system.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_e5090bf757e2582e2690780840c48cfe_1autotoc_md346">
<title>Commands</title><para><table rows="2" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Command  </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Description  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>TimerControlCommand</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Carries a <computeroutput>TimerControlContext</computeroutput> to request a timer state transition (start, pause, stop)  </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_e5090bf757e2582e2690780840c48cfe_1autotoc_md347">
<title>Usage</title><para>Commands are typically issued by game-state listeners or systems when a timer needs to change state:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".cpp"><codeline><highlight class="keyword">auto</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>context<sp/>=<sp/>TimerControlContext{TimerState::Started,<sp/>myTimerId};</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">updateContext.commandBuffer().add&lt;TimerControlCommand&gt;(std::move(context));</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>The command is dispatched via the Visitor pattern - <computeroutput>accept()</computeroutput> delegates to <computeroutput>TimerCommandDispatcher</computeroutput>, which forwards the request to <computeroutput>TimerManager</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
